{"sha": "8cf428bfd3ca967b3d135e311d3e391998a39335", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6OGNmNDI4YmZkM2NhOTY3YjNkMTM1ZTMxMWQzZTM5MTk5OGEzOTMzNQ==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2021-08-26T12:13:27Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2021-08-26T23:12:54Z"}, "message": "libstdc++: Add static assertions for std::function requirements\n\nAdd static assertions to std::function, so that more user-friendly\ndiagnostics are given when trying to store a non-copyable target object.\n\nThese preconditions were added as \"Mandates:\" by LWG 2447, but I'm\ncommitting them separately from implementing that, to allow just this\nchange to be backported more easily.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jonathan Wakely <jwakely@redhat.com>\n\nlibstdc++-v3/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* include/bits/std_function.h (function::function(F)): Add\n\tstatic assertions to check constructibility requirements.", "tree": {"sha": "374a32287341e906b31c7e5f5969cb7dfc5fbb7a", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/374a32287341e906b31c7e5f5969cb7dfc5fbb7a"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/8cf428bfd3ca967b3d135e311d3e391998a39335", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/8cf428bfd3ca967b3d135e311d3e391998a39335", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/8cf428bfd3ca967b3d135e311d3e391998a39335", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/8cf428bfd3ca967b3d135e311d3e391998a39335/comments", "author": {"login": "jwakely", "id": 1254480, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQ0ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1254480?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely", "html_url": "https://github.com/jwakely", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely/fo